overview:
This class allows you interact with DLP API.

First, install @google-cloud/dlp with npm:

$ npm install --save @google-cloud/dlp

If you are running your app on Google Compute Engine, you won't need to worry about supplying connection configuration options to @google-cloud/dlpâ€” we figure that out for you.

However, if you're running your app elsewhere, you will need to provide project details to authenticate API requests.

Google Cloud Platform

var dlp = require('@google-cloud/dlp')();

Elsewhere

var dlp = require('@google-cloud/dlp')({ projectId: 'grape-spaceship-123', keyFilename: '/path/to/keyfile.json' });

The full set of options which can be passed to @google-cloud/dlp are outlined in our Authentication guide.

methods.name: InspectConfig
methods.description: Configuration description of the scanning process. When used with redactContent only info_types and min_likelihood are currently used.

params.name: infoTypes
params.description:
Restricts what info_types to look for. The values must correspond to InfoType values returned by ListInfoTypes or found in documentation. Empty info_types runs all enabled detectors.

This object should have the same structure as InfoType

params.name: minLikelihood
params.description:
Only returns findings equal or above this threshold.

The number should be among the values of Likelihood

params.name: maxFindings
params.description: Limits the number of findings per content item.

params.name: includeQuote
params.description: When true, a contextual quote from the data that triggered a finding is included in the response; see Finding.quote.

params.name: excludeTypes
params.description: When true, excludes type information of the findings.

methods.name: ContentItem
methods.description: Container structure for the content to inspect.

params.name: type
params.description: Type of the content, as defined in Content-Type HTTP header. Supported types are: all "text" types, octet streams, PNG images, JPEG images.

params.name: data
params.description: Content data to inspect or redact.

params.name: value
params.description: String data to inspect or redact.

methods.name: InspectResult
methods.description: All the findings for a single scanned item.

params.name: findings
params.description:
List of findings for an item.

This object should have the same structure as Finding

params.name: findingsTruncated
params.description: If true, then this item might have more findings than were returned, and the findings returned are an arbitrary subset of all findings. The findings list might be truncated because the input items were too large, or because the server reached the maximum amount of resources allowed for a single API call. For best results, divide the input into smaller batches.

methods.name: Finding
methods.description: Container structure describing a single finding within a string or image.

params.name: quote
params.description: The specific string that may be potentially sensitive info.

params.name: infoType
params.description:
The specific type of info the string might be.

This object should have the same structure as InfoType

params.name: likelihood
params.description:
Estimate of how likely it is that the info_type is correct.

The number should be among the values of Likelihood

params.name: location
params.description:
Location of the info found.

This object should have the same structure as Location

params.name: createTime
params.description:
Timestamp when finding was detected.

This object should have the same structure as google.protobuf.Timestamp

methods.name: Location
methods.description: Specifies the location of a finding within its source item.

params.name: byteRange
params.description:
Zero-based byte offsets within a content item.

This object should have the same structure as Range

params.name: codepointRange
params.description:
Character offsets within a content item, included when content type is a text. Default charset assumed to be UTF-8.

This object should have the same structure as Range

params.name: imageBoxes
params.description:
Location within an image's pixels.

This object should have the same structure as ImageLocation

params.name: recordKey
params.description:
Key of the finding.

This object should have the same structure as RecordKey

params.name: fieldId
params.description:
Field id of the field containing the finding.

This object should have the same structure as FieldId

params.name: start
params.description: Index of the first character of the range (inclusive).

params.name: end
params.description: Index of the last character of the range (exclusive).

methods.name: ImageLocation
methods.description: Bounding box encompassing detected text within an image.

params.name: top
params.description: Top coordinate of the bounding box. (0,0) is upper left.

params.name: left
params.description: Left coordinate of the bounding box. (0,0) is upper left.

params.name: width
params.description: Width of the bounding box in pixels.

params.name: height
params.description: Height of the bounding box in pixels.

params.name: inspectConfig
params.description:
Configuration for the inspector.

This object should have the same structure as InspectConfig

params.name: items
params.description:
The list of items to inspect. Up to 100 are allowed per request.

This object should have the same structure as ContentItem

params.name: replaceConfigs
params.description:
The strings to replace findings text findings with. Must specify at least one of these or one ImageRedactionConfig if redacting images.

This object should have the same structure as ReplaceConfig

params.name: imageRedactionConfigs
params.description:
The configuration for specifying what content to redact from images.

This object should have the same structure as ImageRedactionConfig

params.name: infoType
params.description:
Type of information to replace. Only one ReplaceConfig per info_type should be provided. If ReplaceConfig does not have an info_type, the DLP API matches it against all info_types that are found but not specified in another ReplaceConfig.

This object should have the same structure as InfoType

params.name: replaceWith
params.description: Content replacing sensitive information of given type. Max 256 chars.

methods.name: ImageRedactionConfig
methods.description: Configuration for determing how redaction of images should occur.

params.name: infoType
params.description:
Only one per info_type should be provided per request. If not specified, and redact_all_text is false, the DLP API will redacts all text that it matches against all info_types that are found, but not specified in another ImageRedactionConfig.

This object should have the same structure as InfoType

params.name: redactAllText
params.description: If true, all text found in the image, regardless if it matches an info_type, is redacted.

params.name: redactionColor
params.description:
The color to use when redacting content from an image. If not specified, the default is black.

This object should have the same structure as Color

methods.name: Color
methods.description: Represents a color in the RGB color space.

params.name: red
params.description: The amount of red in the color as a value in the interval [0, 1].

params.name: green
params.description: The amount of green in the color as a value in the interval [0, 1].

params.name: blue
params.description: The amount of blue in the color as a value in the interval [0, 1].

params.name: items
params.description:
The redacted content.

This object should have the same structure as ContentItem

params.name: inspectConfig
params.description:
Configuration for the inspector.

This object should have the same structure as InspectConfig

params.name: items
params.description:
The list of items to inspect. Items in a single request are considered "related" unless inspect_config.independent_inputs is true. Up to 100 are allowed per request.

This object should have the same structure as ContentItem

params.name: results
params.description:
Each content_item from the request has a result in this list, in the same order as the request.

This object should have the same structure as InspectResult

params.name: inspectConfig
params.description:
Configuration for the inspector.

This object should have the same structure as InspectConfig

params.name: storageConfig
params.description:
Specification of the data set to process.

This object should have the same structure as StorageConfig

params.name: outputConfig
params.description:
Optional location to store findings. The bucket must already exist and the Google APIs service account for DLP must have write permission to write to the given bucket.

Results are split over multiple csv files with each file name matching the pattern "[operationid][count].csv", for example 3094877188788974909_1.csv. The operation_id matches the identifier for the Operation, and the count is a counter used for tracking the number of files written.

The CSV file(s) contain the following columns regardless of storage type scanned:

  • id
  • info_type
  • likelihood
  • byte size of finding
  • quote
  • time_stamp

    For Cloud Storage the next columns are:

  • file_path
  • start_offset

    For Cloud Datastore the next columns are:

  • project_id
  • namespace_id
  • path
  • column_name
  • offset

    This object should have the same structure as OutputStorageConfig

params.name: storagePath
params.description:
The path to a Google Cloud Storage location to store output.

This object should have the same structure as CloudStoragePath

params.name: infoType
params.description:
The type of finding this stat is for.

This object should have the same structure as InfoType

params.name: count
params.description: Number of findings for this info type.

methods.name: InspectOperationMetadata
methods.description: Metadata returned within GetOperation for an inspect request.

params.name: processedBytes
params.description: Total size in bytes that were processed.

params.name: totalEstimatedBytes
params.description: Estimate of the number of bytes to process.

params.name: infoTypeStats
params.description: This object should have the same structure as InfoTypeStatistics

params.name: createTime
params.description:
The time which this request was started.

This object should have the same structure as google.protobuf.Timestamp

params.name: requestInspectConfig
params.description:
The inspect config used to create the Operation.

This object should have the same structure as InspectConfig

params.name: requestStorageConfig
params.description:
The storage config used to create the Operation.

This object should have the same structure as StorageConfig

params.name: requestOutputConfig
params.description:
Optional location to store findings.

This object should have the same structure as OutputStorageConfig

params.name: name
params.description: The server-assigned name, which is only unique within the same service that originally returns it. If you use the default HTTP mapping, the name should have the format of inspect/results/{id}.

params.name: name
params.description: Identifier of the results set returned as metadata of the longrunning operation created by a call to CreateInspectOperation. Should be in the format of `inspect/results/{id}.

params.name: pageSize
params.description: Maximum number of results to return. If 0, the implementation selects a reasonable value.

params.name: pageToken
params.description: The value returned by the last ListInspectFindingsResponse; indicates that this is a continuation of a prior ListInspectFindings call, and that the system should return the next page of data.

params.name: filter
params.description:
Restricts findings to items that match. Supports info_type and likelihood.

Examples:

  • info_type=EMAIL_ADDRESS
  • info_type=PHONE_NUMBER,EMAIL_ADDRESS
  • likelihood=VERY_LIKELY
  • likelihood=VERY_LIKELY,LIKELY
  • info_type=EMAIL_ADDRESS,likelihood=VERY_LIKELY,LIKELY

params.name: result
params.description:
The results.

This object should have the same structure as InspectResult

params.name: nextPageToken
params.description: If not empty, indicates that there may be more results that match the request; this value should be passed in a new ListInspectFindingsRequest.

params.name: name
params.description: Internal name of the info type.

params.name: displayName
params.description: Human readable form of the info type name.

params.name: categories
params.description:
List of categories this info type belongs to.

This object should have the same structure as CategoryDescription

params.name: category
params.description: Category name as returned by ListRootCategories.

params.name: languageCode
params.description: Optional BCP-47 language code for localized info type friendly names. If omitted, or if localized strings are not available, en-US strings will be returned.

params.name: infoTypes
params.description:
Set of sensitive info types belonging to a category.

This object should have the same structure as InfoTypeDescription

params.name: name
params.description: Internal name of the category.

params.name: displayName
params.description: Human readable form of the category name.

params.name: languageCode
params.description: Optional language code for localized friendly category names. If omitted or if localized strings are not available, en-US strings will be returned.

params.name: categories
params.description:
List of all into type categories supported by the API.

This object should have the same structure as CategoryDescription

methods.name: Likelihood
methods.description: Categorization of results based on how likely they are to represent a match, based on the number of elements they contain which imply a match.
